In mathematics, the '''Horrocks construction''' is a method for constructing [[vector bundle]]s, especially over [[projective space]]s, introduced by {{harvs|txt|first=Geoffrey |last=Horrocks|authorlink= Geoffrey Horrocks|year=1964|loc=section 10}}. His original construction gave an example of an indecomposable rank 2 vector bundle over 3-dimensional projective space, and generalizes to give examples of vector bundles of higher ranks over other projective spaces. The Horrocks construction is used in the [[ADHM construction]] to construct [[instanton]]s over the [[4-sphere]].

