'''Invasion percolation''' is a mathematical model of realistic [[Fluid simulation|fluid distributions]] for slow immiscible fluid invasion in porous media, in [[percolation theory]]. It was introduced by Wilkinson and Willemsen (1983).<ref>David Wilkinson and Jorge F Willemsen, "[http://www.physics.purdue.edu/flow/MMproject/Wilkinson1983.pdf Invasion percolation: a new form of percolation theory]", ''J. Phys. A: Math. Gen.'' 16 (1983) 3365–3376.</ref>
